7 SUMMARY
88 This bill enacts provisions to clarify the relationship of state and local law enforcement
99 agencies, including correctional facilities, and state employees with federal immigration
1100 authorities. The bill:
11 1. Prohibits a law enforcement agency from stopping, investigating, interrogating,
12 arresting or detaining a person for immigration enforcement purposes, including in
13 response to a hold request, immigration detainer or administrative warrant issued by the
14 United States Department of Homeland Security, or allowing the United States Department
15 of Homeland Security access to inmates or inmate information or providing law
16 enforcement agency resources or personnel to assist immigration enforcement activities;
17 2. Clarifies that a law enforcement agency upon a request from the United States
18 Department of Homeland Security may arrest and detain a person and perform other law
19 enforcement duties due to suspected criminal activity or other reasons not solely based on
20 the person's immigration status;
21 3. Establishes the permissible scope of collaboration of a law enforcement agency with
22 a joint law enforcement task force;
23 4. Requires a law enforcement agency to release as soon as possible and detain no
24 longer than 48 hours a person determined to be held solely for immigration enforcement
25 purposes;
26 5. Establishes duties and prohibitions for law enforcement agencies regarding
27 immigration issues of inmates, including requiring the agency to inform an inmate of the
28 inmate's rights prior to interview by an immigration authority and whether the agency
29 intends to comply with a hold request and prohibiting an agency from restricting access to
